snippet: Seven rare California condors, born and bred in captivity, have been released into the wild.    Scientists freed the birds on a mountaintop in Monterey County 2,500 feet above the Big Sur coast on Saturday....
lead_paragraph: Seven rare California condors, born and bred in captivity, have been released into the wild. Scientists freed the birds on a mountaintop in Monterey County 2,500 feet above the Big Sur coast on Saturday.
